MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds //carbonyl/src/blink/* to the visibility lists of the three blink GN
targets that //carbonyl/src/blink:text_capture depends on:

  - //third_party/blink/renderer:inside_blink (the config that defines
    INSIDE_BLINK and BLINK_IMPLEMENTATION)
  - //third_party/blink/renderer/core:core (the blink core component)
  - //third_party/blink/renderer/platform:platform (blink platform)

Also refactors content/renderer/render_frame_impl.cc to delegate text
capture to the new //carbonyl/src/blink:text_capture target:

  - Drops all blink/renderer/core/* and blink/renderer/platform/* includes
    (the M135 cppgc cascade trigger)
  - Removes the ~200-line TextCaptureDevice + RendererService class
    definitions (moved verbatim into the new blink TU)
  - Replaces the render_callback_ lambda body with a thin call to
    carbonyl::text_capture::CaptureFromFrame()
  - Adds //carbonyl/src/blink:text_capture to content/renderer/BUILD.gn deps

After this patch:
  - render_frame_impl.cc has zero blink/renderer/* includes (clean TU)
  - The cppgc cascade cannot fire from this TU
  - --carbonyl-b64-text works again (via the new blink-side entry point)

See: roctinam/carbonyl#28 (this work), #27 (diagnosis), #29 (audit)
